    <p>The Mice (meet­ings, in­cen­tives, con­fer­ences and ex­hi­bi­tions) sec­tor is a key part of Sin­ga­pore’s tourism in­dus­try, with the Repub­lic be­ing the top busi­ness events des­ti­na­tion in the Asia-Pa­cific over the past few years.</p>
    <p>> 34,000</p>
    <p>Num­ber of jobs sup­ported by the Mice ecosys­tem.</p>
    <p>$3.8b</p>
    <p>Value-add con­trib­uted by the Mice in­dus­try in a year.</p>
    <p>0.8%</p>
    <p>Con­tri­bu­tion to Sin­ga­pore’s an­nual gross do­mes­tic prod­uct.</p>
    <p>> 2,400</p>
    <p>Num­ber of jobs and train­ing op­por­tu­ni­ties that more than 220 com­pa­nies have made avail­able in the tourism sec­tor since April.</p>
    <p>> 900</p>
    <p>Num­ber of peo­ple who found jobs or took on new roles in tourism through the SGUnited Jobs and Skills Pro­gramme be­tween April and July.</p>


